4) Write a Python program to perform sum of three given integers. 
       However, if any of the two values are equal then sum will be zero (eg : 2+1+1 = 0)
a=raw_input("enter a value")
b=raw_input("enter b value")
c=raw_input("enter c value")
a=int(a)
b=int(b)
c=int(c)
if a==b or a==c or b==c:
 print("sum is 0")
else:
 print(a+b+c)
  enter a value2             enter a value3
  enter b value3             enter b value3            
  enter c value4             enter c value4    
  9                          sum is 0
   
5) Write a Python program to check whether a year is leap year or not
a=raw_input("enter a year")
a=int(a)
if (a%4==0) and ((a%400==0) or (a%100!=0)):
 print("leap year")
else:
 print("not a leap year")
     enter a year2018               enter a year2020
     not a leap year                leap year


6)Write a program that accepts a sentence and calculate the number of upper case letters and lower case letters.

a=raw_input("enter a string")
up=0
lo=0
for i in a:
 if (i.isupper()):
  up=up+1
 elif (i.islower()):
  lo=lo+1
print("uppercase letters %s"%up)
print("lowercase letters %s"%lo)
   enter a stringHello World!
   uppercase letters 2
   lowercase letters 8

8)Write a program that accepts a sentence and calculate the number of upper case letters and lower case letters.

a=[2,3,4,6,7,8]
b=[]
for i in a:
 if(i%2==0):
  b.append(i)
print(b)
print(sum(b))
   [2, 4, 6, 8]
   20

9) Write a program which accepts a sequence of comma-separated numbers from console and generate a list and a tuple which 
contains every number
a=raw_input("enter values")
b=a.split(',')
b=map(int,b)
print(b)
c=tuple(b)
print(c)
 enter values34,67,55,33,12,98
 [34, 67, 55, 33, 12, 98]
 (34, 67, 55, 33, 12, 98)


